<p>I'm using testNG to run some Selenium tests in parallel, my suite.xml looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "http://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd"&gt; &lt;suite thread-count="20" name="Suite" parallel="methods"&gt;   &lt;test name="Test1" group-by-instances="true" junit="true"&gt;    &lt;classes&gt;       &lt;class name="uk.co.Pack1"/&gt;       &lt;class name="uk.co.Pack2"/&gt;     &lt;/classes&gt;   &lt;/test&gt;  &lt;/suite&gt; </code></pre>  <p><code>Pack1</code> contains 2 tests and <code>Pack2</code> contains 1 test so using <code>parallel="methods"</code> I would expect 3 Chrome browsers to appear but only one does.</p>  <p>If I write each class with its methods in seperate tests, each with a single method specified, then set <code>parallel="tests"</code> it works - however duplicating code like that is not something I like neither best practice.</p>  <p>Can anyone help to why this may be?</p>  <p>Thanks.</p>